HEADWORD: Diphycercal
<hw>Diph`y*cer"cal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>difyh`s</grk> double (<grk>di-</grk> = <grk>di`s-</grk> twice +
<grk>fy`ein</grk> to produce) + <grk>ke`rkos</grk> tail.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Having the tail fin divided into two equal parts
by the notochord, or end of the vertebral column; protocercal. See
<er>Protocercal</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diphygenic</ent>⟦br⟧
